						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is in Chāḷukyan characters. Seems to contain proper names of persons. It is in three parts which are unconnected with one another. <hi rend="bold">A</hi> (on the front wall.)</p>						

						<p> <te>śrīdharayya </te> <hi rend="bold">B</hi> (on A pillar.)</p>						

						<p> <te>śrī Utpattipiḍu </te><note n="17-1">[Reading is <te>śrī Utpattipiḍu[gu]• </te> The last letter, though not clear, can be read ṇ. ḷ. ṟ.]</note> <hi rend="bold">C</hi> (on Another pillar.)</p>						

